                        <h3><a href="#">Guideline Objective(s)</a></h3>
                    <p><div class="content_para"><p>To evaluate the appropriateness of initial radiologic examinations for initial liver lesion characterization</p></div></p>
                        <h3><a href="#">Target Population</a></h3>
                    <p><div class="content_para"><p>Patients with a liver lesion</p></div></p>
                        <h3><a href="#">Interventions and Practices Considered</a></h3>
                    <p><ol style="list-style-type: decimal;">
    <li>Ultrasound (US) abdomen </li>
    <li>Computed tomography (CT) abdomen
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;">
        <li>Without and with contrast </li>
        <li>Without contrast </li>
        <li>With contrast </li>
    </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) abdomen
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;">
        <li>Without and with contrast </li>
        <li>Without contrast </li>
    </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Technetium-99 metastable (Tc-99m) liver scan
    <ul style="list-style-type: disc;">
        <li>Sulfur colloid </li>
        <li>Red blood cell (RBC) </li>
    </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Indium-111 (In-111) somatostatin receptor scintigraphy </li>
    <li>Fluorine-18-2-fluoro-2-deoxy-D-glucose positron emission tomography (FDG-PET)/CT whole body </li>
    <li>Percutaneous image-guided liver biopsy </li>
</ol></p>
